The paper discusses a machine learning approach (ensemble learning) and focuses on accurately quantifying model uncertainty. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper introduces a Bayesian nonparametric approach, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Statistics (cs.ST). The paper also deals with real-world data and its utility, which suggests that it could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions air pollution exposure prediction, which could fall under the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category.
